1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,402
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:03,404 --> 00:00:05,738
<i>At least it used to be</i>

3
00:00:05,740 --> 00:00:07,740
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:07,742 --> 00:00:09,608
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:13,381 --> 00:00:16,048
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:16,050 --> 00:00:17,616
<i>Inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:17,618 --> 00:00:19,618
We're trapped.

8
00:00:19,620 --> 00:00:22,321
Julia:
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:22,323 --> 00:00:24,590
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:24,592 --> 00:00:26,658
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:26,660 --> 00:00:28,460
Can I help you?

12
00:00:30,765 --> 00:00:32,598
Well, what happened to me?

13
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:36,435
You don't remember?
I remember... Electricity.

14
00:00:36,437 --> 00:00:38,337
A little young
to be a nurse, aren't you?

15
00:00:38,339 --> 00:00:39,738
Just a lowly candy striper.

16
00:00:45,279 --> 00:00:48,614
You saved julia. Just like you
saved me when the dome

17
00:00:48,616 --> 00:00:50,249
Came down.
Maybe you're here

18
00:00:50,251 --> 00:00:51,517
To save all of us.

19
00:00:55,656 --> 00:00:57,322
Barbie, put
that weapon down!

20
00:00:57,324 --> 00:00:59,491
One person is responsible
for all this:

21
00:00:59,493 --> 00:01:01,326
Dale "barbie"

22
00:01:01,328 --> 00:01:03,729
<i>Barbara. A warrant has been</i>
<i>issued for his arrest.</i>

23
00:01:03,731 --> 00:01:04,797
<i>He's been charged</i>

24
00:01:04,799 --> 00:01:06,265
With the attempted murders

25
00:01:06,267 --> 00:01:07,800
<i>Of mrs. Shumway and myself.</i>

26
00:01:07,802 --> 00:01:09,268
<i>He's also been charged</i>

27
00:01:09,270 --> 00:01:12,604
With the murders
of max seagrave, otto aguilar

28
00:01:12,606 --> 00:01:14,807
And ms. Seagrave's mother,
agatha.

29
00:01:43,169 --> 00:01:46,839
Big jim:
<i>We will hunt down</i>
<i>the murderer dale barbara.</i>

30
00:01:46,841 --> 00:01:49,174
We will bring him in,
and we'll make him pay.

31
00:01:49,176 --> 00:01:50,676
What if he's hiding
in one of our homes?

32
00:01:50,678 --> 00:01:53,212
Miles, I-I recognize the threat,
believe me.

33
00:01:53,214 --> 00:01:54,680
Then why aren't you
knocking down doors?

34
00:01:54,682 --> 00:01:56,281
Because that's illegal.

35
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:58,217
What would you have me do,
miles? House sweeps?

36
00:01:58,219 --> 00:02:00,385
You can search mine.

37
00:02:04,757 --> 00:02:06,425
Maybe you're right.

38
00:02:06,427 --> 00:02:07,793
But I will
not stomp

39
00:02:07,795 --> 00:02:09,194
On people's rights.

40
00:02:09,196 --> 00:02:11,196
Our constitution
still protects them.

41
00:02:11,198 --> 00:02:13,398
This is still
the United States of america.

42
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,900
Miles:
No, it's not.

43
00:02:14,902 --> 00:02:17,603
It hasn't been for two weeks.
You got to do something, rennie.

44
00:02:17,605 --> 00:02:20,205
all right.

45
00:02:20,207 --> 00:02:22,474
I'm declaring a state
of emergency.

46
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:24,910
That bastard threatens
all of us.

47
00:02:24,912 --> 00:02:27,279
So today we
will perform

48
00:02:27,281 --> 00:02:29,214
House sweeps
as a safety precaution only.

49
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:32,317
And we'll bring barbie
to justice.

50
00:02:32,319 --> 00:02:35,320
I am not turning our town
into a police state

51
00:02:35,322 --> 00:02:36,855
Just because
you say so.

52
00:02:38,859 --> 00:02:40,926
It's not me, linda.

53
00:02:40,928 --> 00:02:42,594
It's the people.

54
00:02:42,596 --> 00:02:44,596
All right, everyone, listen up!

55
00:02:44,598 --> 00:02:46,798
This is not the end
of chester's mill.

56
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,801
This is just the beginning.

57
00:02:49,803 --> 00:02:53,272
For all of you who lost jobs
when this dome came down--

58
00:02:53,274 --> 00:02:56,808
Lawyers and-and bankers like
miles-- we've got jobs for you.

59
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:59,811
We've got a reservoir
that needs to be protected,

60
00:02:59,813 --> 00:03:03,415
Crops that need tending,
streets that need to be cleaned.

61
00:03:03,417 --> 00:03:06,418
Yes, it'll take sacrifice.

62
00:03:06,420 --> 00:03:09,288
But we will survive.

63
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:11,256
This dome can't break us.

64
00:03:11,258 --> 00:03:17,362
and the next year.
And every year after that.

65
00:03:25,572 --> 00:03:28,407
Man:
Sir, the satellites are still
showing no visual on our target.

66
00:03:28,409 --> 00:03:30,275
Nsa creeper.

67
00:03:30,277 --> 00:03:31,543
Man 2:
Finding dale barbara

68
00:03:31,545 --> 00:03:33,812
- Is essential.
- good luck, dude.

69
00:03:33,814 --> 00:03:35,280
Until we make contact,

70
00:03:35,282 --> 00:03:36,949
The operation
cannot move forward.

71
00:03:36,951 --> 00:03:39,351
I want eyes
on that unidentified object.

72
00:03:39,353 --> 00:03:40,886
Man:
Sir, yes, sir.

73
00:03:40,888 --> 00:03:43,956
Man 2:
Any idea where the hell
that egg thing is, soldier?

74
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:53,398
Oh, my god.

75
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:56,235
That's what burned me.

76
00:03:56,237 --> 00:03:58,303
Man:
No coordinates on the egg, sir.

77
00:03:58,305 --> 00:04:00,305
But any new information
will be delivered immediately.

78
00:04:00,307 --> 00:04:02,541
Man 2:
It won't mean a thing
until we locate barbara.

79
00:04:02,543 --> 00:04:05,844
He's the only one inside
with the necessary expertise.

80
00:04:08,848 --> 00:04:11,383
What's it doing?

81
00:04:11,385 --> 00:04:13,518
I think it's mad we
didn't kill big jim.

82
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:15,454
Angie, we can't
do that.

83
00:04:15,456 --> 00:04:18,323
We all saw the same vision
at the big dome, joe.

84
00:04:18,325 --> 00:04:18,991
It wants him dead.

85
00:04:18,993 --> 00:04:20,993
Why?
I don't know.

86
00:04:20,995 --> 00:04:23,795
Maybe so that he doesn't
kill your monarch.

87
00:04:23,797 --> 00:04:25,030
You think big jim's
gonna kill barbie?

88
00:04:25,032 --> 00:04:28,967
It sure sounds
like he wants to.
We need to help him, then.

89
00:04:28,969 --> 00:04:30,602
You guys, shut up.

90
00:04:30,604 --> 00:04:32,471
We don't even know that barbie's
the monarch anyway.

91
00:04:32,473 --> 00:04:34,006
Come on. Who else could it be?

92
00:04:34,008 --> 00:04:36,842
any one of us?

93
00:04:36,844 --> 00:04:39,578
Angie:
Well, we know
it's not junior.

94
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:41,580
Not the way he
ran off last night.

95
00:04:41,582 --> 00:04:44,583
Trust me. It's barbie.

96
00:04:44,585 --> 00:04:47,953
He's gonna get us out.

97
00:04:47,955 --> 00:04:50,789
When the butterfly hatches,
you'll see.

98
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:52,524
When the butterfly hatches?

99
00:04:52,526 --> 00:04:54,393
The monarch will be crowned.

100
00:04:55,828 --> 00:04:57,963
I don't see
how it crowns anybody

101
00:04:57,965 --> 00:05:00,632
If it's trapped
inside that little dome.

102
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:07,472
I just feel when it comes
out of its chrysalis,

103
00:05:07,474 --> 00:05:10,008
something's gonna change.

104
00:05:11,077 --> 00:05:12,744
Carolyn:
What are you doing?

105
00:05:12,746 --> 00:05:14,946
No, no. Let me see.

106
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,583
Carolyn:
Oh, my god.

107
00:05:19,552 --> 00:05:21,987
What is that?

108
00:05:21,989 --> 00:05:23,822
It's, like...

109
00:05:23,824 --> 00:05:25,624
The dome's heart.

110
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,361
What do you mean, "heart"?

111
00:05:29,363 --> 00:05:32,631
We think it's the source
that powers the whole thing.

112
00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:37,602
How long have you had this?

113
00:05:37,604 --> 00:05:41,606
We found it
just before mom died.

114
00:05:41,608 --> 00:05:46,111
This... Is the thing
in the woods?

115
00:05:46,113 --> 00:05:48,647
That showed you alice?

116
00:05:48,649 --> 00:05:51,650
Yeah.

117
00:05:51,652 --> 00:05:55,053
And it sent me home
so I could tell her good-bye.

118
00:05:59,392 --> 00:06:01,026
All right, you need
to move this.

119
00:06:01,028 --> 00:06:03,829
They're gonna be searching
all the houses. Hide it.

120
00:06:04,797 --> 00:06:06,732
You're not mad?

121
00:06:06,734 --> 00:06:10,669
Norrie, honey,
I'm on your side. Always.

122
00:06:12,805 --> 00:06:15,741
And I don't trust
big jim with anything.

123
00:06:15,743 --> 00:06:19,010
Especially this.

124
00:06:19,012 --> 00:06:20,812
Take it to ben's.

125
00:06:20,814 --> 00:06:22,514
We can trust him.

126
00:06:22,516 --> 00:06:23,782
You're not coming?

127
00:06:23,784 --> 00:06:26,518
I have business with big jim.

128
00:06:27,621 --> 00:06:31,089
You do not treat any of
your neighbors with disrespect.

129
00:06:31,091 --> 00:06:33,091
You do not damage property.

130
00:06:33,093 --> 00:06:36,161
And you do not kill
dale barbara.

131
00:06:38,097 --> 00:06:40,165
Go serve and protect.

132
00:06:41,601 --> 00:06:43,435
Morning, sheriff.

133
00:06:43,437 --> 00:06:44,736
Tank's empty. Sorry.

134
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:46,571
But thanks for the use
of your car.

135
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:48,907
No worries. You need
an extra hand today?

136
00:06:48,909 --> 00:06:50,509
Sure do. Let's go.

137
00:06:50,511 --> 00:06:52,577
All right.

138
00:06:55,648 --> 00:06:58,150
Junior:
Dad!

139
00:06:59,986 --> 00:07:01,653
What's going on, junior?
Dad...

140
00:07:01,655 --> 00:07:03,955
I-I was looking
for you all night.

141
00:07:04,891 --> 00:07:07,092
Dad, you're in danger.

142
00:07:07,094 --> 00:07:08,593
Someone's gonna
try to kill you.

143
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:10,495
Maybe barbie,
maybe someone else.

144
00:07:10,497 --> 00:07:11,630
How do you know this?

145
00:07:11,632 --> 00:07:13,932
Uh... I-I just know.

146
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:18,437
You got to... Get a hold
of yourself, junior.

147
00:07:18,439 --> 00:07:19,738
Focus.

148
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:22,040
Listen, I got
a job for you.

149
00:07:22,042 --> 00:07:24,576
Barbie shot julia shumway
yesterday.

150
00:07:26,579 --> 00:07:28,146
That son of a bitch.

151
00:07:28,148 --> 00:07:30,048
So I sent some people
over to the clinic,

152
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:31,683
Keep an eye out,
make sure he doesn't...

153
00:07:31,685 --> 00:07:33,985
Show up to finish
what he started.

154
00:07:33,987 --> 00:07:37,522
But I need somebody
I can trust on the inside,

155
00:07:37,524 --> 00:07:40,659
Guarding her door,
protecting her.

156
00:07:40,661 --> 00:07:42,127
Can I count on you?

157
00:07:42,129 --> 00:07:43,662
Yes, sir.

158
00:07:43,664 --> 00:07:46,565
She's ever gonna
regain consciousness,

159
00:07:46,567 --> 00:07:50,769
But, by chance, if she does
wake up and start talking,

160
00:07:50,771 --> 00:07:53,505
You need to get on that walkie
and let me know.

161
00:07:53,507 --> 00:07:54,840
No one else.

162
00:07:54,842 --> 00:07:56,641
Just me.

163
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:59,911
Okay. But, dad...

164
00:07:59,913 --> 00:08:01,746
Just be careful today.

165
00:08:01,748 --> 00:08:04,649
Okay.

166
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,653
Big jim, got a minute?

167
00:08:08,655 --> 00:08:10,622
Pretty busy this morning, dodee.

168
00:08:10,624 --> 00:08:12,724
No, you have to come
to the radio station.

169
00:08:12,726 --> 00:08:14,159
Ah, I don't want
to overwhelm the public

170
00:08:14,161 --> 00:08:15,594
With more announcements.
My receiver

171
00:08:15,596 --> 00:08:16,995
Picked up
the military.

172
00:08:16,997 --> 00:08:18,563
They're searching
for barbie.

173
00:08:19,899 --> 00:08:21,600
Barbie?

174
00:08:21,602 --> 00:08:23,768
They're searching
for something else, too.

175
00:08:29,909 --> 00:08:30,909
shh!

176
00:08:30,911 --> 00:08:32,777
Shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh.

177
00:08:32,779 --> 00:08:34,713
Hey, hey.

178
00:08:34,715 --> 00:08:38,850
Look, there is a lot of people
looking for you.

179
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:40,252
I know, I know.
Listen.

180
00:08:40,254 --> 00:08:41,853
Everything that they're
saying about me...

181
00:08:41,855 --> 00:08:43,021
None of it is true.

182
00:08:43,023 --> 00:08:44,723
It's big jim, to...
I believe you.

183
00:08:44,725 --> 00:08:46,825
You do?

184
00:08:47,994 --> 00:08:50,228
Got a lot of good reasons
not to trust jim rennie.

185
00:08:50,230 --> 00:08:52,297
Julia's still
at the clinic.

186
00:08:52,299 --> 00:08:54,933
Now, if she wakes up,
he's gonna kill her.

187
00:08:54,935 --> 00:08:56,635
Why?

188
00:08:56,637 --> 00:08:59,604
That it wasn't actually
me that shot her,

189
00:08:59,606 --> 00:09:02,774
Now he doesn't have me to use
as his scapegoat anymore.

190
00:09:02,776 --> 00:09:03,942
Okay, so what do you
want me to do?

191
00:09:03,944 --> 00:09:06,177
Candy stripers.

192
00:09:06,179 --> 00:09:07,646
You guys
have key cards

193
00:09:07,648 --> 00:09:08,647
To the clinic's
back entrance.

194
00:09:08,649 --> 00:09:09,781
Am I right?

195
00:09:09,783 --> 00:09:10,782
Yeah.
Yeah.

196
00:09:10,784 --> 00:09:12,584
So help me save julia.

197
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:32,571
Junior:
How's she doing?

198
00:09:32,573 --> 00:09:34,940
She was lucky
to survive.

199
00:09:34,942 --> 00:09:36,241
There's no telling
what kind of

200
00:09:36,243 --> 00:09:37,943
Neurological damage
she might have.

201
00:09:37,945 --> 00:09:39,611
You think she'll come out of it?

202
00:09:39,613 --> 00:09:41,079
I'm not a doctor,
junior.

203
00:09:41,081 --> 00:09:42,714
Yeah, but...

204
00:09:42,716 --> 00:09:44,616
You're kind of as close
to a doctor as we've got.

205
00:09:44,618 --> 00:09:46,351
And I have other patients
to check on.

206
00:09:46,353 --> 00:09:48,219
I'll keep an eye on julia.

207
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:55,660
Angie:
So what's the plan?

208
00:09:55,662 --> 00:09:57,629
I'm gonna hot-wire
the ambulance.

209
00:09:57,631 --> 00:10:00,632
Then what?

210
00:10:00,634 --> 00:10:02,701
And then we use
your key card to get us in,

211
00:10:02,703 --> 00:10:04,736
We get julia out...

212
00:10:04,738 --> 00:10:05,971
You drive us away.

213
00:10:05,973 --> 00:10:08,340
Okay, what about
the guards?

214
00:10:08,342 --> 00:10:10,875
Oh, they'll swing around
to the front sooner or later.

215
00:10:10,877 --> 00:10:11,977
No, not them.

216
00:10:11,979 --> 00:10:14,045
What about
the guards inside?

217
00:10:14,047 --> 00:10:15,747
Big jim must know
you're coming for her.

218
00:10:15,749 --> 00:10:16,915
He might have moved her already.

219
00:10:18,217 --> 00:10:19,317
Yeah, maybe.

220
00:10:20,753 --> 00:10:24,155
There are a lot of ifs here.

221
00:10:25,225 --> 00:10:26,858
Listen.

222
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:28,960
Big jim has taken out
every single person

223
00:10:28,962 --> 00:10:30,829
That stood in his way.

224
00:10:30,831 --> 00:10:33,164
Julia is his
last loose end.

225
00:10:33,166 --> 00:10:35,166
Now, are you in...

226
00:10:35,168 --> 00:10:36,868
Or are you out?

227
00:10:46,712 --> 00:10:49,881
No sign of the military
for over a week--

228
00:10:49,883 --> 00:10:52,784
Not since they tried
to blow us to kingdom come.

229
00:10:52,786 --> 00:10:54,753
Now they want barbie?

230
00:10:54,755 --> 00:10:55,887
I told you,
all right?

231
00:10:55,889 --> 00:10:57,722
He's only
part of it.

232
00:10:57,724 --> 00:11:00,258
The military's
looking for an egg?

233
00:11:00,260 --> 00:11:02,127
Yeah, and...

234
00:11:02,129 --> 00:11:03,762
And I've seen it.

235
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:10,669
What's it do?

236
00:11:10,671 --> 00:11:13,772
I'm not sure,
but it burned the crap

237
00:11:13,774 --> 00:11:15,106
Out of my hand.

238
00:11:16,376 --> 00:11:18,243
One second.

239
00:11:18,245 --> 00:11:20,712
I promised phil
I'd keep the music going.

240
00:11:20,714 --> 00:11:22,213
All right, just...

241
00:11:22,215 --> 00:11:23,882
Just don't
touch anything.

242
00:11:26,687 --> 00:11:28,153
Man:
...On the move.

243
00:11:28,155 --> 00:11:30,255
Thermal photography shows
the unidentified object

244
00:11:30,257 --> 00:11:32,123
Has been transported
from the woods

245
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:33,958
To two miles northeast
of town center.

246
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:36,094
holy hell.

247
00:11:36,096 --> 00:11:37,328
Man 2:
Any sign of barbie?

248
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:39,297
Man:
Negative, sir.

249
00:11:39,299 --> 00:11:41,399
Man 2:
Any idea who's
in charge in there?

250
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:43,968
Man:
Sir, the ranking official
is a james rennie.

251
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:51,076
Man 2:
Is he a viable contact
for this mission?

252
00:11:52,379 --> 00:11:54,379
Man:
...Cox, I would not
recommend that.

253
00:11:55,882 --> 00:11:57,115
Cox:
Your reasoning, soldier?

254
00:11:57,117 --> 00:12:01,920
Our uavs did a full perimeter
sweep on the dome wall.

255
00:12:01,922 --> 00:12:03,722
One drone caught surveillance

256
00:12:03,724 --> 00:12:05,290
Of this rennie
murdering the town reverend

257
00:12:05,292 --> 00:12:06,758
At the bridge roadblock.

258
00:12:21,474 --> 00:12:23,007
New job, mr. Alcott?

259
00:12:23,009 --> 00:12:24,843
No need for banks
anymore, ben.

260
00:12:24,845 --> 00:12:27,445
There's always
garbage, though.

261
00:12:29,248 --> 00:12:30,448
Joe:
Ben.

262
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:31,783
Ben!

263
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:34,352
Come on.

264
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:41,760
What's that?

265
00:12:41,762 --> 00:12:43,061
Joe:
We have something

266
00:12:43,063 --> 00:12:44,929
We have to hide
from the sweeps.

267
00:12:44,931 --> 00:12:48,333
The gestapo hit my house
a while back.

268
00:12:48,335 --> 00:12:50,101
Any chance we can stash it?

269
00:12:50,103 --> 00:12:51,970
My stash house
is your stash house.

270
00:13:14,326 --> 00:13:15,827
More guards?

271
00:13:15,829 --> 00:13:17,028
Junior.

272
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:19,497
Doing big jim's dirty work.

273
00:13:20,867 --> 00:13:23,334
Coward.

274
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:28,006
He's got a walkie.

275
00:13:30,109 --> 00:13:32,911
But I think I can take
him out before he uses it.

276
00:13:32,913 --> 00:13:34,279
No.

277
00:13:34,281 --> 00:13:36,414
No, what?

278
00:13:41,287 --> 00:13:43,354
Let me.

279
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:46,491
Calm down, dodee.

280
00:13:46,493 --> 00:13:50,428
I am calm. Really.

281
00:13:52,364 --> 00:13:54,432
But what they said you did...

282
00:13:55,301 --> 00:13:56,968
I thought what happened

283
00:13:56,970 --> 00:13:59,337
To reverend coggins
was an accident.

284
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:02,507
No, <i>he</i> was an accident
waiting to happen.

285
00:14:02,509 --> 00:14:05,043
I mean, he almost...

286
00:14:05,045 --> 00:14:08,546
Burned down the whole town
the day after we got stuck here.

287
00:14:08,548 --> 00:14:10,448
He's a liability.

288
00:14:12,418 --> 00:14:15,320
You don't know the
whole story, dodee.

289
00:14:15,322 --> 00:14:18,389
And neither do
those peeping toms

290
00:14:18,391 --> 00:14:21,326
With their eyes in the sky.

291
00:14:22,928 --> 00:14:25,396
How many accidents
have there been?

292
00:14:26,967 --> 00:14:29,400
The ones
that you said barbie killed...

293
00:14:29,402 --> 00:14:32,370
Barbie is no saint,
believe that.

294
00:14:32,372 --> 00:14:34,305
But he didn't do it, did he?

295
00:14:34,307 --> 00:14:37,041
Oh, he did more
than enough

296
00:14:37,043 --> 00:14:40,311
To deserve whatever punishment
he's got coming to him.

297
00:14:40,313 --> 00:14:42,313
Every one of those people got...

298
00:14:42,315 --> 00:14:44,315
What they had coming to them.

299
00:14:44,317 --> 00:14:49,120
They were threats
to chester's mill.

300
00:14:49,122 --> 00:14:53,491
And all I've ever done was
protect the people of this town.

301
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:55,894
Think I'd hurt them?

302
00:14:55,896 --> 00:14:58,229
Are you...?

303
00:15:00,299 --> 00:15:02,634
No. I don't think that.

304
00:15:02,636 --> 00:15:04,636
Oh, good.

305
00:15:04,638 --> 00:15:07,205
So let's help each other
out here,

306
00:15:07,207 --> 00:15:09,574
Focus on this egg.

307
00:15:09,576 --> 00:15:11,342
You have that photograph of it.

308
00:15:11,344 --> 00:15:12,577
Wh-where'd you take it?

309
00:15:12,579 --> 00:15:16,047
It was at joe mcalister's barn.

310
00:15:16,049 --> 00:15:18,483
I didn't even remember
until this morning.

311
00:15:18,485 --> 00:15:22,153
I was thinking... It could
even be the generator.

312
00:15:22,155 --> 00:15:24,923
The generator?

313
00:15:24,925 --> 00:15:26,357
For what?

314
00:15:26,359 --> 00:15:28,559
The dome.

315
00:15:28,561 --> 00:15:32,096
Look, maybe
if you get this thing,

316
00:15:32,098 --> 00:15:34,599
You could bring down the dome.

317
00:15:36,568 --> 00:15:40,405
I can get
it for you.

318
00:15:40,407 --> 00:15:42,941
I can help.

319
00:15:42,943 --> 00:15:45,310
All right, I can be useful.

320
00:15:45,312 --> 00:15:48,146
Well, dodee...

321
00:15:48,148 --> 00:15:51,382
You're already very useful.

322
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:58,389
But that dome can't come down.

323
00:15:58,391 --> 00:16:00,325
Not now.

324
00:16:05,465 --> 00:16:07,465
Big jim?

325
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:09,233
Yeah, what is it, honey?

326
00:16:11,036 --> 00:16:14,372
You're a sick... Bastard.

327
00:16:14,374 --> 00:16:16,441
And one day,

328
00:16:16,443 --> 00:16:18,543
Everyone's gonna know it.

329
00:16:21,748 --> 00:16:24,215
And they're gonna smile
when you die.

330
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:01,219
♪

331
00:17:30,649 --> 00:17:31,749
Linda? Linda, it's jim.

332
00:17:31,751 --> 00:17:33,451
Where are you?

333
00:17:33,453 --> 00:17:35,586
Sweeping the
southwest quadrant.

334
00:17:35,588 --> 00:17:37,288
The radio station's on fire.

335
00:17:37,290 --> 00:17:40,158
What?

336
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,559
Dodee was covering for me.

337
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:43,227
Is she okay?
Jim, any word

338
00:17:43,229 --> 00:17:44,395
On dodee?

339
00:17:44,397 --> 00:17:45,129
I don't know.

340
00:17:45,131 --> 00:17:48,232
The, uh, fire volunteers
are gathering,

341
00:17:48,234 --> 00:17:49,734
But you need to get down there.

342
00:17:49,736 --> 00:17:51,102
Could it be arson?

343
00:17:51,104 --> 00:17:53,071
No idea.

344
00:17:53,073 --> 00:17:55,073
It's barbie.

345
00:17:55,075 --> 00:17:58,109
We've been broadcasting
info about him night and day.

346
00:17:58,111 --> 00:17:59,544
Jim, I'm on it.

347
00:17:59,546 --> 00:18:00,678
All right, be careful, linda.

348
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,580
When you find barbie,
you call me.

349
00:18:02,582 --> 00:18:04,615
Roger. Phil, come on.

350
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:12,423
So, you really think
this is the engine?

351
00:18:12,425 --> 00:18:14,325
It could be our way out of here.

352
00:18:14,327 --> 00:18:15,827
It's awesome.
It's like a lava lamp.

353
00:18:15,829 --> 00:18:17,462
Hey, don't touch it!

354
00:18:17,464 --> 00:18:19,163
Last person who
did got hurt.

355
00:18:19,165 --> 00:18:21,165
All you have to do
is keep it covered,

356
00:18:21,167 --> 00:18:24,102
Keep your parents away from it
and keep an eye on it.

357
00:18:24,104 --> 00:18:26,571
Where you gonna be?

358
00:18:26,573 --> 00:18:30,274
Home. I got to stop angie
from doing something stupid.

359
00:18:30,276 --> 00:18:31,609
It's in good hands.

360
00:18:31,611 --> 00:18:33,511
Thanks, ben.

361
00:18:33,513 --> 00:18:35,746
We'll be back to get it later.

362
00:18:42,421 --> 00:18:43,421
Hey.

363
00:18:43,423 --> 00:18:45,423
Angie.

364
00:18:45,425 --> 00:18:48,126
What are you doing here?

365
00:18:48,128 --> 00:18:50,428
Just helping out
like I used to.

366
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:56,134
Are you okay
after what we saw last night?

367
00:18:56,136 --> 00:18:58,136
Sure.

368
00:18:58,138 --> 00:18:59,237
Then why'd you run off?

369
00:18:59,239 --> 00:19:00,605
To protect my dad.

370
00:19:00,607 --> 00:19:03,508
To stop anyone
from hurting him.

371
00:19:05,677 --> 00:19:07,712
Do you trust your dad?
Of course I do.

372
00:19:07,714 --> 00:19:09,147
You didn't always.

373
00:19:09,149 --> 00:19:11,682
When we were going out,
you called him a fraud.

374
00:19:15,555 --> 00:19:17,722
Barbie shot her yesterday.

375
00:19:17,724 --> 00:19:19,457
Is that what your dad said?

376
00:19:20,692 --> 00:19:23,361
He wouldn't lie
to me about that.

377
00:19:23,363 --> 00:19:25,363
But if barbie didn't shoot her,

378
00:19:25,365 --> 00:19:27,365
Then julia's the only witness,
right?

379
00:19:27,367 --> 00:19:30,768
Did big jim tell you
what to do if she woke up?

380
00:19:34,339 --> 00:19:37,175
Leave me alone, angie.

381
00:19:37,177 --> 00:19:39,243
Junior, I'm sorry.

382
00:19:40,245 --> 00:19:42,413
My head is a mess. I...

383
00:19:42,415 --> 00:19:45,383
I don't know
what anything means anymore.

384
00:19:45,385 --> 00:19:48,486
I just need someone to talk to.

385
00:19:50,255 --> 00:19:53,758
Someone... Or me?

386
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:55,826
You.

387
00:19:55,828 --> 00:19:58,229
You're the only one

388
00:19:58,231 --> 00:20:00,298
Who understands
what I'm going through.

389
00:20:03,969 --> 00:20:05,836
But can we go somewhere private?

390
00:20:05,838 --> 00:20:08,272
I feel like she can hear
everything we say.

391
00:20:08,274 --> 00:20:10,975
I said I'd watch her.

392
00:20:10,977 --> 00:20:13,344
Just for a minute.

393
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:17,348
Please.

394
00:20:20,319 --> 00:20:22,386
Hmm.

395
00:20:25,357 --> 00:20:27,491
I need you.

396
00:20:45,477 --> 00:20:47,979
we found her
body in the station.

397
00:20:47,981 --> 00:20:50,314
There was nothing
we could do.

398
00:20:50,316 --> 00:20:52,383
Thanks.

399
00:20:54,386 --> 00:20:57,922
Phil... I'm so sorry.

400
00:21:00,459 --> 00:21:02,393
Why'd he do it?

401
00:21:02,395 --> 00:21:06,564
Why did he do it?

402
00:21:06,566 --> 00:21:08,633
Dodee never hurt anyone.

403
00:21:09,868 --> 00:21:12,336
I don't know.

404
00:21:12,338 --> 00:21:15,473
But barbie won't
get away with it.

405
00:21:16,541 --> 00:21:18,609
I promise.

406
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:31,455
I just don't know how much more
of this I can take.

407
00:21:31,457 --> 00:21:35,893
Hey, you don't have
to do it alone.

408
00:21:35,895 --> 00:21:38,429
I'm always gonna
be with you.

409
00:21:49,509 --> 00:21:51,309
It feels so good

410
00:21:51,311 --> 00:21:52,610
Just to hold you again.

411
00:21:52,612 --> 00:21:54,412
Mmm.

412
00:21:54,414 --> 00:21:57,782
I know. It does.

413
00:22:25,644 --> 00:22:27,511
You taste like cigarettes.

414
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,120
Junior?!

415
00:22:48,401 --> 00:22:49,533
Miss hill, let me
tell you how much

416
00:22:49,535 --> 00:22:50,568
We don't have
time for this.

417
00:22:50,570 --> 00:22:52,603
Let me tell you,
mr. Rennie,

418
00:22:52,605 --> 00:22:54,972
How much a lawyer knows
about illegal searches.

419
00:22:54,974 --> 00:22:57,475
If you don't have
a search warrant--

420
00:22:57,477 --> 00:23:00,444
Which you do not-- you're gonna
need one of four things:

421
00:23:00,446 --> 00:23:02,580
Consent from the owner,

422
00:23:02,582 --> 00:23:05,082
Clear visibility of the inside,

423
00:23:05,084 --> 00:23:07,685
A suspect
already under arrest...

424
00:23:07,687 --> 00:23:09,487
Or exigent circumstances.

425
00:23:09,489 --> 00:23:10,588
I don't know
what you call

426
00:23:10,590 --> 00:23:17,795
I call it just one more day
in this damn hellhole...

427
00:23:17,797 --> 00:23:20,564
And respectfully request
that you leave.

428
00:23:20,566 --> 00:23:23,601
Request respectfully declined.

429
00:23:25,704 --> 00:23:27,805
No! Stop this now!

430
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:31,575
Stop it!
Get off of me!

431
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:33,677
Don't you
touch my mother!

432
00:23:33,679 --> 00:23:35,579
Norrie, no!

433
00:23:35,581 --> 00:23:36,881
Back away now!
Norrie!

434
00:23:36,883 --> 00:23:38,416
Norrie!

435
00:23:38,418 --> 00:23:39,583
Joe:
Let them go!

436
00:23:41,187 --> 00:23:43,020
Norrie!
Norrie, stop!

437
00:23:43,022 --> 00:23:45,890
Wonder what you're so bent
out of shape me seeing in here.

438
00:23:55,634 --> 00:23:57,902
What the hell?

439
00:23:58,904 --> 00:23:59,970
Where is it?

440
00:23:59,972 --> 00:24:01,772
Where's what?
Don't play games

441
00:24:01,774 --> 00:24:04,175
That damn egg.
I know all about it,

442
00:24:04,177 --> 00:24:05,609
And I know what it's for.

443
00:24:07,078 --> 00:24:09,680
We have no idea
what you're talking about.

444
00:24:09,682 --> 00:24:11,115
Take these two to the station.

445
00:24:11,117 --> 00:24:13,651
On what charges?

446
00:24:13,653 --> 00:24:14,819
Obstruction of justice.

447
00:24:14,821 --> 00:24:16,754
Mom!

448
00:24:16,756 --> 00:24:18,489
Norrie!
Let go of me!

449
00:24:18,491 --> 00:24:19,490
I'll fix it!

450
00:24:19,492 --> 00:24:21,892
I'll get you out!

451
00:24:23,228 --> 00:24:24,728
Barbie!

452
00:24:26,198 --> 00:24:29,233
Linda, barbie's at the clinic!
Barbie's at the clinic!

453
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:48,953
Linda:
Junior, I'm 30 seconds away!

454
00:24:58,563 --> 00:25:00,664
I love you.

455
00:25:04,236 --> 00:25:05,669
Barbie, we got to go!

456
00:25:07,706 --> 00:25:09,139
Drive fast! Go!
Stay hidden!
What? Why?!

457
00:25:09,141 --> 00:25:11,275
They're not gonna come looking
if they've got me! Go!

458
00:25:11,277 --> 00:25:12,843
What are you doing?!
What are you doing?!

459
00:25:12,845 --> 00:25:14,278
Go! Go! Get her
out of here now!

460
00:25:33,298 --> 00:25:36,033
Put your hands
on your head!

461
00:25:36,035 --> 00:25:38,002
Get your ass
to the ground!

462
00:25:56,254 --> 00:25:57,688
Hey!

463
00:25:57,690 --> 00:25:58,956
Get-get back.

464
00:26:04,296 --> 00:26:05,996
Jim, got him.

465
00:26:07,032 --> 00:26:08,766
Good.

466
00:26:08,768 --> 00:26:11,602
But angie mcalister took off
with julia.

467
00:26:13,939 --> 00:26:14,972
Don't worry.

468
00:26:14,974 --> 00:26:16,640
We'll get her, too.

469
00:26:26,851 --> 00:26:29,053
Norrie?

470
00:26:29,055 --> 00:26:31,755
Norrie, come over here
and talk to me, please.

471
00:26:36,227 --> 00:26:38,062
Angie was right.

472
00:26:38,064 --> 00:26:40,331
Angie was right about what?

473
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:44,735
We should've killed big jim
when we had the chance.

474
00:26:44,737 --> 00:26:47,204
Why would the dome want us
to do that?

475
00:26:47,206 --> 00:26:49,873
Look what he's doing, joe.

476
00:26:49,875 --> 00:26:52,209
Pulling all these
nazi moves?

477
00:26:52,211 --> 00:26:55,613
Breaking into your barn
like he owns the place?

478
00:26:55,615 --> 00:26:57,047
That doesn't mean
we should kill him.

479
00:26:57,049 --> 00:27:02,052
What do you think's gonna happen
when he finds barbie?

480
00:27:02,054 --> 00:27:05,189
Your monarch
won't be crowned, joe.

481
00:27:05,191 --> 00:27:08,792
It's more like "the monarch gets
his head chopped off."

482
00:27:11,030 --> 00:27:12,763
You know that quote?

483
00:27:12,765 --> 00:27:16,367
"the only thing necessary
for the triumph of evil

484
00:27:16,369 --> 00:27:19,069
Is for good people
to do nothing."

485
00:27:27,712 --> 00:27:30,114
That's us, joe.

486
00:27:36,355 --> 00:27:39,156
Look at little miss
well-behaved.

487
00:27:40,792 --> 00:27:42,793
Joe?

488
00:27:42,795 --> 00:27:44,895
Joe, I've known you
your whole life.

489
00:27:44,897 --> 00:27:45,996
You're a decent kid.

490
00:27:45,998 --> 00:27:49,299
A smart kid.

491
00:27:49,301 --> 00:27:51,068
Not like your sister.

492
00:27:51,070 --> 00:27:52,102
Angie's smart.

493
00:27:52,104 --> 00:27:56,774
Throwing in all her chips
on a losing hand.

494
00:27:56,776 --> 00:27:58,409
Aiding and abetting
a violent fugitive.

495
00:27:58,411 --> 00:28:00,110
She may be past help, but you...

496
00:28:00,112 --> 00:28:03,881
You, joe...
You can fix this.

497
00:28:03,883 --> 00:28:05,849
Tell me where it is...

498
00:28:05,851 --> 00:28:08,185
And we'll forget
any of this happened.

499
00:28:09,754 --> 00:28:11,889
I'll let you go
home-- both you

500
00:28:11,891 --> 00:28:13,757
And your, uh...

501
00:28:13,759 --> 00:28:15,225
Your new friend.

502
00:28:17,162 --> 00:28:19,063
If this...

503
00:28:19,065 --> 00:28:22,933
Egg thing really is
the generator of the dome

504
00:28:22,935 --> 00:28:26,770
Like I've heard,

505
00:28:26,772 --> 00:28:30,908
You keeping it squirreled away
is a very serious offense:

506
00:28:30,910 --> 00:28:34,712
Impeding a lawful investigation.

507
00:28:40,251 --> 00:28:42,152
You got something to say,
little lady?

508
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:49,460
So why do they
call you <i>big</i> jim?

509
00:28:49,462 --> 00:28:51,962
You're just some loser
trying to scare kids.

510
00:28:51,964 --> 00:28:54,031
I'm sorry.

511
00:28:57,969 --> 00:28:59,803
I didn't quite hear that.

512
00:29:02,941 --> 00:29:04,975
You want to say that again?

513
00:29:04,977 --> 00:29:08,779
You... Don't...

514
00:29:08,781 --> 00:29:11,248
Scare... Me.

515
00:29:14,220 --> 00:29:17,087
You're old enough to understand
how this goes.

516
00:29:17,089 --> 00:29:19,056
The easy way is you tell me

517
00:29:19,058 --> 00:29:20,491
What I want to know,

518
00:29:20,493 --> 00:29:23,293
You walk out
that door, you're free.

519
00:29:23,295 --> 00:29:25,262
Now, the hard way...

520
00:29:25,264 --> 00:29:27,264
Well, let's just say

521
00:29:27,266 --> 00:29:30,200
Your mother has come
to so much grief already.

522
00:29:31,870 --> 00:29:33,203
It'd be a shame

523
00:29:33,205 --> 00:29:36,206
If you caused her
any more misery.

524
00:29:39,177 --> 00:29:40,077
Norrie!

525
00:29:52,023 --> 00:29:54,124
I gave you kids a chance.

526
00:29:57,495 --> 00:30:00,364
You want to burn with barbie...

527
00:30:00,366 --> 00:30:02,099
Be my guest.

528
00:30:08,072 --> 00:30:10,174
Linda:
Heading back to the station now.

529
00:30:10,176 --> 00:30:11,975
We have barbie in custody.

530
00:30:11,977 --> 00:30:13,811
No eyes yet on julia shumway.

531
00:30:13,813 --> 00:30:16,213
Last seen in an ambulance
being driven by angie mcalister

532
00:30:16,215 --> 00:30:18,382
Away from the clinic.

533
00:30:38,203 --> 00:30:40,070
That really necessary?

534
00:30:40,072 --> 00:30:42,606
Big jim tell you
to do it?

535
00:30:48,379 --> 00:30:51,882
All of these things
that I'm being accused of?

536
00:30:51,884 --> 00:30:53,984
I would never hurt julia.

537
00:30:53,986 --> 00:30:55,219
You got to know that.

538
00:30:55,221 --> 00:30:58,055
Yeah? What about her husband?

539
00:31:02,327 --> 00:31:04,361
That's what I thought.

540
00:31:09,300 --> 00:31:10,868
Here to report a crime?

541
00:31:10,870 --> 00:31:13,337
I won't leave the premises
until my daughter

542
00:31:13,339 --> 00:31:15,005
And joe mcalister
are released.

543
00:31:15,007 --> 00:31:19,309
It's a public building.
You stay as long as you like.

544
00:31:19,311 --> 00:31:22,179
So, what's
the good word?

545
00:31:22,181 --> 00:31:24,081
Nothing on julia
and angie mcalister,

546
00:31:24,083 --> 00:31:25,916
But we got an apb out.

547
00:31:25,918 --> 00:31:27,284
Sooner or later,
we'll get them.

548
00:31:27,286 --> 00:31:29,553
Okay, well, sooner
would be better than later.

549
00:31:29,555 --> 00:31:31,922
A woman in julia's condition
needs watching.

550
00:31:31,924 --> 00:31:34,658
Do we know if she's come out
of her coma yet?

551
00:31:34,660 --> 00:31:36,393
No clue.

552
00:31:36,395 --> 00:31:38,428
What about barbie?

553
00:31:38,430 --> 00:31:41,031
He's downstairs in lockup.

554
00:31:41,033 --> 00:31:42,299
Good.

555
00:31:43,401 --> 00:31:45,168
Now what?

556
00:31:46,237 --> 00:31:48,105
We let him sweat.

557
00:32:31,349 --> 00:32:33,550
What are you doing?!

558
00:32:33,552 --> 00:32:35,185
Get off me!

559
00:32:36,988 --> 00:32:39,122
Barbie, don't tell him
anything!

560
00:32:39,124 --> 00:32:41,091
We'll be okay.

561
00:32:41,093 --> 00:32:42,659
Hey.

562
00:32:42,661 --> 00:32:45,128
Where are you taking them?

563
00:32:49,067 --> 00:32:52,436
Let's just call it
an undisclosed location.

564
00:32:53,438 --> 00:32:54,671
I swear,
if you hurt those kids...

565
00:32:54,673 --> 00:32:56,239
Tell you what,
seeing as you're

566
00:32:56,241 --> 00:32:58,608
In no position
to make any threats,

567
00:32:58,610 --> 00:33:00,377
How about I do the talking?

568
00:33:00,379 --> 00:33:03,513
So, here's
the situation.

569
00:33:03,515 --> 00:33:05,549
You're going to confess
to the charges,

570
00:33:05,551 --> 00:33:08,285
And you're going to do it
in public.

571
00:33:09,554 --> 00:33:11,755
It's not going to happen.

572
00:33:11,757 --> 00:33:14,324
Well, that's
your prerogative.

573
00:33:14,326 --> 00:33:18,595
What will happen if you
choose not to cooperate.

574
00:33:18,597 --> 00:33:21,999
Won't be long before we catch up
with angie mcalister.

575
00:33:22,001 --> 00:33:25,135
And when we do, we'll charge her
as an accessory

576
00:33:25,137 --> 00:33:29,106
To your crimes, seeing as
she's been so helpful to you.

577
00:33:29,108 --> 00:33:31,708
Her brother joe
and that little firecracker

578
00:33:31,710 --> 00:33:34,378
He's been rubbing noses with,

579
00:33:34,380 --> 00:33:37,647
It's no leap to link them
to the death of dodee weaver,

580
00:33:37,649 --> 00:33:40,217
Seeing as dodee knew

581
00:33:40,219 --> 00:33:41,618
All about this mysterious object

582
00:33:41,620 --> 00:33:43,120
That they're taking
such great pains

583
00:33:43,122 --> 00:33:45,055
To keep to themselves.

584
00:33:46,057 --> 00:33:47,691
And there's your redhead.

585
00:33:50,695 --> 00:33:54,531
If she ever comes out
of her coma,

586
00:33:54,533 --> 00:33:58,602
She'll go down
for hiring a known criminal

587
00:33:58,604 --> 00:34:03,607
To murder her husband
for the insurance money.

588
00:34:03,609 --> 00:34:09,079
Now, that's as cold
as cold-blooded gets.

589
00:34:14,485 --> 00:34:18,255
So what do you say, barbie?

590
00:34:18,257 --> 00:34:20,323
We got a deal?

591
00:34:22,627 --> 00:34:26,696
You let the kids go...

592
00:34:26,698 --> 00:34:29,433
And you leave angie
and julia alone...

593
00:34:32,737 --> 00:34:35,338
...And I'll say
what you want me to say.

594
00:34:35,340 --> 00:34:37,808
I'd say we shake hands, but...

595
00:34:41,312 --> 00:34:43,447
Hey, jim.

596
00:34:46,350 --> 00:34:48,718
How do I know
you're going to keep your word?

597
00:34:48,720 --> 00:34:50,754
You don't.

598
00:35:01,866 --> 00:35:03,667
Are you all right?

599
00:35:03,669 --> 00:35:07,270
If that man did
anything to you...

600
00:35:07,272 --> 00:35:09,473
I'm all right, mom.

601
00:35:09,475 --> 00:35:12,109
We need to check
on the mini-dome,

602
00:35:12,111 --> 00:35:13,510
Make sure it's safe.

603
00:35:14,779 --> 00:35:16,713
Put a tail on those kids.

604
00:35:16,715 --> 00:35:17,781
Why?

605
00:35:17,783 --> 00:35:20,217
They're hiding something.

606
00:35:20,219 --> 00:35:21,852
Something that might
help us understand

607
00:35:21,854 --> 00:35:23,487
Why we're trapped
under this thing.

608
00:35:23,489 --> 00:35:24,621
Something like what?

609
00:35:24,623 --> 00:35:26,656
It's tough to say, but...

610
00:35:26,658 --> 00:35:28,892
Could be our way out.

611
00:35:31,762 --> 00:35:33,163
You really think so?

612
00:35:33,165 --> 00:35:35,532
If we're lucky.

613
00:35:45,443 --> 00:35:47,444
What happened
at the clinic, junior?

614
00:35:47,446 --> 00:35:49,146
I'm sorry.
I tried my best...

615
00:35:49,148 --> 00:35:51,648
All right, well, you get
a second chance now.
I...

616
00:35:51,650 --> 00:35:53,683
Get out there and find
your little girlfriend,

617
00:35:53,685 --> 00:35:56,586
Bring her and julia shumway
back here, pronto.

618
00:36:03,461 --> 00:36:04,661
What's the problem, junior?

619
00:36:04,663 --> 00:36:07,697
What's so important
about finding julia?

620
00:36:08,499 --> 00:36:09,599
Barbie's locked up.

621
00:36:09,601 --> 00:36:11,234
He can't hurt her anymore.

622
00:36:11,236 --> 00:36:14,204
Well, he can't, that's true.

623
00:36:14,206 --> 00:36:17,874
But who knows what other
traitors he's got out there

624
00:36:17,876 --> 00:36:19,576
Ready to pull
the trigger for him?

625
00:36:19,578 --> 00:36:22,679
Better safe than
sorry, I say.

626
00:36:24,315 --> 00:36:26,683
I love you, dad.

627
00:36:28,886 --> 00:36:30,954
But don't lie to me.

628
00:36:32,623 --> 00:36:36,259
That would be very bad
for both of us.

629
00:36:39,830 --> 00:36:43,567
He confessed, son.

630
00:36:43,569 --> 00:36:46,469
He confessed
everything.

631
00:36:46,471 --> 00:36:49,406
And soon, he's gonna stand
in front of the town

632
00:36:49,408 --> 00:36:51,508
And confess to them, too.

633
00:36:51,510 --> 00:36:52,842
Okay?

634
00:36:53,844 --> 00:36:56,279
Let's get back
to work.

635
00:37:01,452 --> 00:37:03,220
Oh, I was gonna
ask you:

636
00:37:03,222 --> 00:37:06,389
Last time you saw her--
uh, julia...

637
00:37:07,558 --> 00:37:09,259
...Was she conscious?

638
00:37:10,628 --> 00:37:12,495
Okay.

639
00:37:12,497 --> 00:37:14,564
Okay.

640
00:37:31,582 --> 00:37:32,749
What's wrong?

641
00:37:32,751 --> 00:37:35,418
Your freaky sphere
is going crazy, man.

642
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:37,420
Show us.

643
00:37:43,495 --> 00:37:44,794
Julia?

644
00:37:44,796 --> 00:37:45,929
Hey, hey, it's angie.

645
00:37:45,931 --> 00:37:47,530
You need to be quiet.

646
00:37:47,532 --> 00:37:49,299
Here.

647
00:37:52,738 --> 00:37:54,938
Shh...

648
00:37:58,476 --> 00:38:00,543
Somebody shot me.

649
00:38:02,046 --> 00:38:03,747
Do you remember who?

650
00:38:06,050 --> 00:38:08,318
A woman.

651
00:38:13,991 --> 00:38:15,725
Where are we?

652
00:38:15,727 --> 00:38:16,960
We're in the clinic.

653
00:38:16,962 --> 00:38:18,895
In the storage room.

654
00:38:18,897 --> 00:38:20,964
It may be stupid, but...

655
00:38:20,966 --> 00:38:23,667
I thought it was the last
place they'd look for us.

656
00:38:23,669 --> 00:38:25,602
Barbie and I snuck
you out of the clinic

657
00:38:25,604 --> 00:38:27,037
In an ambulance earlier.

658
00:38:27,039 --> 00:38:28,938
But I-I doubled back
and left the ambulance

659
00:38:28,940 --> 00:38:30,740
Behind a billboard
on the road.

660
00:38:30,742 --> 00:38:33,443
Got you down here on
a service elevator.

661
00:38:34,579 --> 00:38:37,380
Big jim
has been telling everyone

662
00:38:37,382 --> 00:38:38,982
Barbie's the one who shot you.

663
00:38:40,751 --> 00:38:42,986
What? He's...
Okay, okay.

664
00:38:42,988 --> 00:38:45,555
He's lying.

665
00:38:45,557 --> 00:38:47,891
What you just said...

666
00:38:47,893 --> 00:38:50,360
Is exactly why
we have to hide you.

667
00:38:52,596 --> 00:38:53,863
Where's barbie?

668
00:38:58,969 --> 00:39:00,704
Listen up.

669
00:39:00,706 --> 00:39:02,972
Please, can I have
your attention?

670
00:39:05,576 --> 00:39:07,744
We've all been through
a hell of a lot

671
00:39:07,746 --> 00:39:09,713
These past two weeks.

672
00:39:09,715 --> 00:39:13,450
Lived through
this unprecedented event.

673
00:39:13,452 --> 00:39:16,619
Suffered some terrible losses.

674
00:39:16,621 --> 00:39:18,722
And it may seem
like the rules that

675
00:39:18,724 --> 00:39:21,591
All of us were raised with
no longer apply.

676
00:39:21,593 --> 00:39:23,626
Let me tell you this.

677
00:39:23,628 --> 00:39:27,063
Even though we may be separated
from the world outside,

678
00:39:27,065 --> 00:39:28,998
Even though there's
no government

679
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:31,668
Beyond this hall that you see
in front of you today,

680
00:39:31,670 --> 00:39:35,638
Rules are necessary.

681
00:39:35,640 --> 00:39:38,541
And when rules are broken...

682
00:39:38,543 --> 00:39:40,610
There must be justice.

683
00:39:41,645 --> 00:39:43,546
And where appropriate,

684
00:39:43,548 --> 00:39:45,815
Punishment.

685
00:39:45,817 --> 00:39:48,418
Dale barbara stands accused
of the murders

686
00:39:48,420 --> 00:39:51,154
Of maxine
and agatha seagrave,

687
00:39:51,156 --> 00:39:54,057
Otto aguilar
and peter shumway,

688
00:39:54,059 --> 00:39:57,160
And for the attempted murder
of julia shumway.

689
00:39:57,162 --> 00:40:00,697
I've brought him
before you here today

690
00:40:00,699 --> 00:40:03,600
To answer
for those crimes.

691
00:40:04,703 --> 00:40:06,870
Cover your ears!

692
00:40:37,803 --> 00:40:39,869
What do I do?

693
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:51,714
here, lay back.

694
00:40:56,654 --> 00:40:59,155
What do you think
they'll do to him?

695
00:41:02,860 --> 00:41:04,727
They're gonna kill him.

696
00:41:04,729 --> 00:41:09,065
To the charges brought
against you, mr. Barbara...

697
00:41:09,067 --> 00:41:11,835
How do you plead?

698
00:41:23,981 --> 00:41:25,648
What is that?

699
00:41:48,639 --> 00:41:51,107
I asked you a question,
mr. Barbara.

700
00:41:51,109 --> 00:41:52,976
How do you plead?

701
00:41:59,717 --> 00:42:01,084
Not guilty.

702
00:42:01,086 --> 00:42:03,887
